    {
      "time": 1776402193005,
      "link": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7449846611876405248?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7449846611876405248%2C7450770823730208768%29&dashCommentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_comment%3A%287450770823730208768%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7449846611876405248%29",
      "text": "The nano-analyzer result is the key data point -- it shows the capability isn't locked to frontier compute. Once cheap open-weight models can reproduce CVE-worthy findings with one-file tooling, defenders need to assume attackers have the same leverage.",
