    {
      "time": 1776344587517,
      "link": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7449846611876405248?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7449846611876405248%2C7450529208797233152%29&dashCommentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_comment%3A%287450529208797233152%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7449846611876405248%29",
      "text": "What gets interesting is when these scanners stop being a research demo and start living inside release workflows. If a 5.1B open-weights model can surface a 20-year-old networking issue plus new kernel candidates, the next question is not whether it finds things, it’s how teams decide exploitability, ownership, and ship/no-ship thresholds when the model has no source-level intuition, just pattern pressure.",
